umd.cs.shop2
Class LogicalAtom

java.lang.Object
  |
  +--umd.cs.shop2.LogicalAtom
public class LogicalAtom
extends java.lang.Object

An individual assertion in SHOP2 syntax. A typical example of the text of a LogicalAtom is "(on block1 block2)". The text may also contain nested lists, e.g., "(route-explored ((p1 p2) (p2 p3) (p3 p1)))".

LogicalAtoms are used in JSHOP2 as elements of State obects (used as an input to the Shop constructor for embedded use). In addition, LogicalAtoms are used as elements in the Shop addList and Shop.deleteList fields.
